1) Re-enable & highlight the actual filter icon (minimal change)

This restores the icon display for filtered headers and colors it.

/* ensure selector specificity and that this loads after Kendo CSS */
.k-grid th.k-filtered > .k-grid-filter,
.k-grid th.k-filtered > .k-header-column-menu {
    color: #0078d7 !important;   /* your highlight color */
    fill: #0078d7 !important;
}

/* undo Kendo's "hide" rules just for filtered header icons */
.k-grid th.k-filtered > .k-grid-filter .k-icon,
.k-grid th.k-filtered > .k-header-column-menu .k-icon,
.k-grid th.k-filtered > .k-grid-filter,
.k-grid th.k-filtered > .k-header-column-menu {
    text-indent: 0 !important;       /* show the glyph */
    overflow: visible !important;    /* allow it to render */
    width: auto !important;
    height: auto !important;
    display: inline-block !important;
    line-height: 1 !important;
    vertical-align: middle !important;
}


Notes:

This directly counters the text-indent: -99999px + overflow: hidden rules only for filtered header icons.

Make sure this CSS file loads after Kendo’s CSS so !important is not strictly required but safe to keep.

Test: apply a filter, inspect the <th>; you should now see the filter glyph in blue.

If you still don’t see the glyph, Kendo may be rendering an SVG instead of font-glyph or the header text content may be something else — in that case use option 2.

2) (Recommended) Add a tiny status badge to the column header when filtered

This avoids touching the icon glyph and is robust across Kendo versions/themes.

/* small colored dot on the right of filtered headers */
.k-grid th.k-filtered {
    position: relative; /* ensure pseudo-element positions correctly */
}

/* the dot */
.k-grid th.k-filtered::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 10px;                 /* tweak to align to your header height */
    right: 10px;               /* tweak to keep it close to the icon */
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: #0078d7;       /* highlight color */
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px rgba(0,120,215,0.12);
    pointer-events: none;
    z-index: 5;
}


Why this is nice:
